Mark Mader

Hi, Terry. I think we have the opportunity to land larger, but the beautiful thing is not a requirement, right. So if you have someone who really wants to accelerate right out of the gate and want to consume a premium platform thing with Brandfolder included and fully digitized a large workflow, they can do so. But I would say that the ability for them to maintain that optionality still remains critical. We still see evidence of teams within large departments at really large companies wanting to have that earned enterprise approach. So it's important as we come up with these new offerings, we're not forcing the customer's hand, we're giving them an option.

And I think that's where as Gene said, the a la carte approach or the fully packaged bundle approach, I think it’s something that is still very much needed. I would say, though, that with Brandfolder was a good example, where we had a couple of new wins that were in the high five figure range. And it's a wonderful performance by that team.

Terrell Tillman

